ZH: 这个国家压制了言论自由。
EN: This country suppresses freedom of speech.

ZH: 这部电影以压制个人追求为主题。
EN: This film has the theme of suppressing personal pursuits.

ZH: 他试图压制自己的情绪。
EN: He tried to suppress his emotions.

ZH: 这种药物可以压制咳嗽的症状。
EN: This medication can suppress symptoms of coughing.

ZH: 这个政府一直在压制反对派。
EN: This government has been suppressing the opposition.

ZH: 她努力压制住了内心的恐惧。
EN: She tried hard to suppress her inner fear.

ZH: 这个制度用来压制一切异议者。
EN: This system is used to suppress any dissenters.

ZH: 为了平息骚乱，军队必须压制暴力。
EN: To quell the riot, the military must suppress violence.

ZH: 他用力压制住了怒火。
EN: He forcefully suppressed his anger.

ZH: 这个独裁者通过暴力手段压制异议声音。
EN: This dictator suppresses dissenting voices through violent means.

ZH: 这个制度压制了人们的创造力。
EN: This system suppresses people's creativity.

ZH: 我们不能一直压制自己的情感。
EN: We can't keep suppressing our emotions all the time.

ZH: 随着时间的推移，他压制的痛苦逐渐释放了出来。
EN: Over time, the pain he suppressed gradually came out.

ZH: 这个政府的目标是压制一切抗议活动。
EN: The aim of this government is to suppress all protest activities.

ZH: 她用言辞尽量压制住泪水。
EN: She tried to suppress her tears with her words.

ZH: 这个法律被用来压制少数民族的权利。
EN: This law is being used to suppress the rights of minorities.

ZH: 当时政府以暴力方式压制了反对派的抗议。
EN: The government at that time suppressed the opposition's protests through violent means.

ZH: 压制罪犯是维护社会安全的重要手段。
EN: Suppressing criminals is an important means to maintain social security.

ZH: 这个军事行动旨在压制恐怖分子。
EN: This military operation aims to suppress terrorists.

ZH: 需要有强力措施来压制犯罪活动。
EN: Strong measures are needed to suppress criminal activities.
